                                                                                                                                Indicators and status

                                                                                                                                Progress steps

                                                                                                                                Stable

                                                                                                                                A progress steps component is a series of milestones that provides an overview of a complex process or multistep flow, like a transportation itinerary or account creation flow. Progress steps help guide and encourage users as they use our apps.

                                                                                                                                Usage
                                                                                                                                Spec
                                                                                                                                Status & changelog
                                                                                                                                Common alternative names
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                Steps left, tracker, steps to complete, horizontal steps, vertical steps, multi-step wizard, itinerary, path, timeline, meter


                                                                                                                                Questions, comments, feedback?

                                                                                                                                Leave a comment in Figma or reach out to us on Slack.

                                                                                                                                #base-design-support


                                                                                                                                Anatomy

                                                                                                                                At least 3 steps are required to create a progress steps component.


                                                                                                                                Usage

                                                                                                                                Use a progress steps component to help users to understand how far they have progressed in a multi-step process and how many steps remain before completion.

                                                                                                                                This is especially helpful when users complete tasks in a complex flow with multiple phases, such as signup, checkout, or an onboarding experience.


                                                                                                                                Figma component how-to

                                                                                                                                (Vertical)

                                                                                                                                Typically progress steps are custom-built with the progress steps element- vertical. You can also detach the default component as a template and rearrange or add more progress items.

                                                                                                                                First, to use the progress steps component, familiarize yourself with its list item elements and their hidden variants.

                                                                                                                                Progress steps
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                Progress steps are made with the Progress element - List items. The leading artwork has path lines running from top to bottom, so when the list items stack together, they mimic one connecting path line.

                                                                                                                                Artwork sizes come in X Small, Small, Medium, and Large. The X Small icons are used for bullet lists or stops in an itinerary and are not recommended to be customized into any other icons. The Small, Medium, and Large artworks follow the same rules as List item leading content.

                                                                                                                                Progress element - List item
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                In a Progress steps item, both top and bottom path lines are visible by default. If a Progress list item is the first or last in a list you can select the hidden Path component and toggle the top or bottom path off from the variant panel on the right.


                                                                                                                                Hidden Path variants
                                                                                                                                Add notes

                                                                                                                                Going deeper into the hidden Path variants, you can also pick different style path lines. To make the path lines work with auto layout and expand with the list content, we've made the lines in frames so a toggled-off path line is an invisible frame so the artwork can still stay in its intended position.

                                                                                                                                The path lines come in solid and dashed lines with enabled and disabled states. The solid lines can be recolored to transit line colors if needed.


                                                                                                                                Change leading content

                                                                                                                                Do
                                                                                                                                You can change artwork size by selecting different variants in the progress steps component.
                                                                                                                                Don’t
                                                                                                                                Don't try to change the instance of the leading content. The component is hidden, so you won't find it.

                                                                                                                                Artwork none

                                                                                                                                Do
                                                                                                                                If you want a path straight through, pick Artwork none in the Artwork properties.
                                                                                                                                Don’t
                                                                                                                                Try not to hide the artwork to connect the lines. Yes, you'll achieve the same effect, but if you need to change the color of the line, you'll have to do it for the top and the bottom line now.

                                                                                                                                Artwork X Small

                                                                                                                                Do
                                                                                                                                The X small artwork variant is only used for stops, and it can be a circle or a square by changing the Shape property.
                                                                                                                                Don’t
                                                                                                                                We don't recommend any other icons because the icon size is still 16X16 with a frame clipping so the lines can connect. If it changes into any other icons, the lines will pierce.

                                                                                                                                How to build a Progress steps component:

                                                                                                                                1. Pick a Progress element - List item with the desired artwork size and trailing content.

                                                                                                                                2. Customize the artwork and visibility of path lines with hidden Path variants.

                                                                                                                                3. Customize the style of path lines with hidden Path line variants.
